---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Manual - Makonome">
  <main>
    <header>
      <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to home</a>
      <h1>Manual</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Learn how to get the most out of Makonome</p>
    </header>

    <nav class="toc">
      <h2>Contents</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="#basics">Basic Controls</a></li>
        <li><a href="#time-signatures">Time Signatures & Subdivisions</a></li>
        <li><a href="#beat-accents">Beat Accents & Muting</a></li>
        <li><a href="#gap-trainer">Gap Trainer</a></li>
        <li><a href="#tempo-changer">Tempo Changer</a></li>
        <li><a href="#sounds">Sounds & Settings</a></li>
        <li><a href="#practice">Practice Tracking</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <section class="content">
      <article id="basics">
        <h2>Basic Controls</h2>
        <p>The main screen shows a circular BPM dial. Drag around the dial to adjust tempo, or tap the center to type a specific BPM value.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>BPM Range:</strong> 40 to 400 BPM</li>
          <li><strong>Tap Tempo:</strong> Tap the hand icon repeatedly to set tempo by feel</li>
          <li><strong>Play/Stop:</strong> The large green button starts and stops the metronome</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article id="time-signatures">
        <h2>Time Signatures & Subdivisions</h2>
        <p>Tap the music note icon to configure your time signature and subdivision.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Beats per bar:</strong> 1 to 16 beats</li>
          <li><strong>Subdivisions:</strong> Quarter notes, eighth notes, sixteenth notes, or triplets</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article id="beat-accents">
        <h2>Beat Accents & Muting</h2>
        <p>Tap any beat indicator at the top to cycle through states:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Normal:</strong> Regular click sound</li>
          <li><strong>Accented:</strong> Louder, higher-pitched click (filled circle)</li>
          <li><strong>Muted:</strong> Silent beat (dashed circle)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Use this to create custom accent patterns or practice specific rhythmic figures.</p>
      </article>

      <article id="gap-trainer">
        <h2>Gap Trainer</h2>
        <p>The Gap Trainer helps you develop your internal sense of time by periodically muting the metronome.</p>
        <p>Access it from the <strong>⋯</strong> menu and configure:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Normal bars:</strong> How many bars the metronome plays</li>
          <li><strong>Muted bars:</strong> How many bars of silence follow</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The pattern repeats: play → silence → play → silence. Try to keep steady time during the silent sections!</p>
      </article>

      <article id="tempo-changer">
        <h2>Tempo Changer</h2>
        <p>Gradually increase tempo over time to push your limits progressively.</p>
        <p>Access it from the <strong>⋯</strong> menu and configure:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>BPM Increment:</strong> How much to increase (1-10 BPM)</li>
          <li><strong>Interval Mode:</strong> Increase every N bars, or every N seconds</li>
          <li><strong>Target BPM:</strong> Optionally set a maximum tempo to stop at</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Great for building speed on exercises or working up to a target tempo.</p>
      </article>

      <article id="sounds">
        <h2>Sounds & Settings</h2>
        <p>Customize your click sound in Settings:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Click sounds:</strong> Click, Clave, Woodblock, Cowbell</li>
          <li><strong>Pitch adjustment:</strong> Raise or lower the click pitch</li>
          <li><strong>Volume:</strong> Tap the speaker icon on the main screen</li>
          <li><strong>Haptic feedback:</strong> Feel the beat (experimental feature)</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article id="practice">
        <h2>Practice Tracking</h2>
        <p>Makonome automatically logs your practice sessions. View your history in the Practice tab to see:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Total practice time</li>
          <li>Session dates and durations</li>
          <li>Tempo and settings used</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </section>

    <footer>
      <p>&copy; 2025 Makonome. Built with ♥ for musicians.</p>
    </footer>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  header {
    padding: 2rem 0 3rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .toc {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    border: 1px solid #333;
  }

  .toc h2 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .toc ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .toc a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  article {
    scroll-margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  article h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #333;
  }

  article p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  article ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  article li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  article li::before {
    content: "•";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  article strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  footer {
    border-top: 1px solid #333;
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding: 2rem 0;
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }
</style>
